CLI Host Examples
===============================================================================

CLI host examples should demonstrate environment reads and stdout/stderr output.

1. Environment read
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

```mech
+> @env := cli/env

home := @env/HOME
```

2. Stdout line output
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

```mech
+> @out := cli/stdout

@out/line <- "Hello from Mech"
```

3. Stderr text output
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

```mech
+> @err := cli/stderr

@err/text <- "warning"
```

4. Future example folder
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A user-facing CLI host example should be added under:

```text
examples/hosts/cli/
```

until the examples tree is reorganized.
